# MCU Dataflow Tracer

Trace data flow through the insulation resistance measurement pipeline.

## Pipeline Stages

```
[Stage 1] ADC + DMA (1kHz)
  ADC0 channels → 16-bit, HW 32x avg, DMA transfer
  Files: Drivers/adc.c, Drivers/dma.c
       ↓ DMA15 ISR (1ms)

[Stage 2] Moving Average (adc_gathering.c)
  accumulate_adc_sample() → adc_ma_sum[2][32]
  10 samples/window, 32 window ring buffer
       ↓ get_adc_ma_history_ptr()

[Stage 3] Sliding Window Average (measure.c, 200ms)
  read_and_average_samples() → sum_sliding_window()
  20 windows (200 samples) average
       ↓

[Stage 4] DC Calibration (calibration.c)
  calibration_adjust_dc_voltage() → 2-point linear
  calibration_adjust_current() → zero offset + linear
       ↓

[Stage 5] Resistance (measure.c)
  validate_measurement() → R = V / I
       ↓

[Stage 6] Temperature Compensation (measure.c)
  compensate_resistance_to_reference_temp()
  k_t = exp2f(-(base-test)/slope)
       ↓

[Stage 7] Index Calculation (insulation_index.c)
  PI: R(t1)/R(t2) × 10
  DAR: R(t1)/R(t2) × 10
  RI: R at ri_t (absolute)
       ↓

[Stage 8] Host Communication (module_management.c)
  module_write(32000, measure_data)
  Units: V, μA, MΩ
```

## Shared Variables and Synchronization

| Resource | Producer | Consumer | Sync |
|----------|----------|----------|------|
| adc_ma_sum[2][32] | DMA15 ISR | aggregation_task | CRITICAL_SECTION |
| ma_index, samples_in_window | DMA15 ISR | aggregation_task | volatile + CRIT_SEC |
| measure_1s_indexed_buffer | aggregation_task | index_eval_task | indexed_buffer internal |
| published_index etc. | index_eval_task | module_management | publish_lock mutex |

## Unit Conversion Map

```
ADC counts (uint16_t) → float (sliding avg) → V/A (calibrated)
  → Ω (R=V/I) → Ω (temp compensated) → MΩ (÷1e6) → μA (×1e6, current only)
```

## Timing

| Layer | Period | Processing |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| PIT0 ISR | 1ms | ADC trigger |
| DMA15 ISR | ~1ms | Sample accumulate |
| aggregation_task | 200ms | Average, calibrate, resistance |
| index_eval_task | 1s | PI/DAR/RI index calculation |
